TIMEEntertainmentcelebrities + READ ARTICLEBlake Shelton and Gwen Stefani performed their new duet, “Go Ahead and Break My Heart” during Monday night’s episode of The Voice .
Stefani, 46, and Shelton, 39—coaches on The Voice —have been dating for months after both divorcing their spouses.
Stefani has said the budding romance provided inspiration for many of the songs on her new album, This Is What the Truth Feels Like.
Stefani also admitted that her recent single, “Make Me Like You” was about the country musician, after she performed the song at the Grammys in February.
